headline.main: Fifth Year of War Starts This Morning

lead_paragraph: Europe today entered the fifth year of the war, which began at 5 A.M. on Sept. 1, 1939, when German troops drove across the Polish frontier in Upper Silesia and German bombers opened their air attack at Gdynia, Cracow and Katowice.
abstract: War start 4th anniv: war start recalled
